Wash and dry produce.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the
@red pepper jam{1%unit}, and a capful of @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(two capfuls for 4 servings). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{} (large bowl for 4 servings), combine remaining red
pepper jam, half the remaining vinegar (all for 4), and a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Add
@spinach{2.5%ounce} to bowl with dressing; toss to combine. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if desired.

Spread @flour tortillas{2%unit} with as much red pepper mayo as you like.

> TIP: If tortillas are rigid or sticking to each other, wrap in a damp
> paper towel and microwave for 20-30 seconds.

Evenly fill the bottom two-thirds of each tortilla with @prosciutto{2%ounce},
@mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, and half the spinach salad. Starting from the
bottom of the tortilla, roll up tightly, then trim off the curved short
edges; discard trim. Slice each rolled-up tortilla crosswise into 6-8
pieces.

Divide roll-ups, cut sides down, between plates.

> TIP: Arrange roll-ups right up against each other to prevent unraveling.

Serve with remaining spinach salad on the side.